WEBVTT

1
00:00:23.101 --> 00:00:27.063
- Okay, okay.
- That's enough of that. -


2
00:00:27.105 --> 00:00:28.773
Hello, loyal viewers!

3
00:00:28.815 --> 00:00:32.652
Like me, you probably never
thought this day would come.


4
00:00:32.693 --> 00:00:35.738
I see some old friends.
I see new friends.


5
00:00:35.780 --> 00:00:38.533
I see friends who frankly
should put some pants on


6
00:00:38.574 --> 00:00:40.159
and venture outside
occasionally.


7
00:00:40.201 --> 00:00:42.453
Seriously, get some sun!

8
00:00:42.495 --> 00:00:44.956
But, for those who
are just joining us,


9
00:00:44.997 --> 00:00:47.834
here's a little something
to catch you up in the form


10
00:00:47.875 --> 00:00:52.296
of my incredibly exciting
superhero origin story!


11
00:00:53.548 --> 00:00:56.050
Metrocity,
a city full of danger,


12
00:00:56.092 --> 00:01:00.555
and only Metro Man was strong
enough to defend it from evil.


13
00:01:01.681 --> 00:01:04.267
Until I totally
kicked his butt! -


14
00:01:07.437 --> 00:01:09.355
That's me, Megamind.

15
00:01:09.397 --> 00:01:11.649
Incredibly handsome
criminal genius


16
00:01:11.691 --> 00:01:14.485
and master of all villainy.

17
00:01:15.653 --> 00:01:18.865
But without a hero to fight,
I felt lonely.


18
00:01:18.906 --> 00:01:23.286
So I created a new superhero
to play with named Titan.


19
00:01:23.327 --> 00:01:27.081
Unfortunately, he was a worse
villain than I ever was.


20
00:01:30.168 --> 00:01:32.628
It was then that I realized

21
00:01:32.670 --> 00:01:35.131
my destiny was not
to be a supervillain,


22
00:01:35.173 --> 00:01:37.800
but a superhero.

23
00:01:37.842 --> 00:01:41.471
- I defeated Titan
and saved the day. -


24
00:01:43.806 --> 00:01:47.393
I became Megamind,
defender of Metrocity.


25
00:01:47.435 --> 00:01:49.353
But little did I know,

26
00:01:49.395 --> 00:01:52.648
my greatest challenge
was yet to come.


27
00:02:02.658 --> 00:02:04.494
Blue Mackerel: You're in
my personal space, bro.


28
00:02:04.535 --> 00:02:06.621
Red Snapper: Oh, well,
excuse me for swimming!


29
00:02:06.662 --> 00:02:08.915
I don't think that
was a sincere apology!


30
00:02:08.956 --> 00:02:11.250
- It's not!
- Big King Fish: Both of you, clam up!


31
00:02:13.544 --> 00:02:14.837
We got work to do.

32
00:02:14.879 --> 00:02:17.715
Go fish.

33
00:02:26.891 --> 00:02:28.017
Here goes.

34
00:02:35.608 --> 00:02:37.693
There it is.

35
00:02:37.735 --> 00:02:41.280
Catch of the day.

36
00:02:48.746 --> 00:02:51.374
Ooh, this little baby's
gonna be worth a fortune


37
00:02:51.416 --> 00:02:53.209
on the black fish market!

38
00:03:01.926 --> 00:03:04.178
You'd think with all
the time you guys spent


39
00:03:04.220 --> 00:03:06.973
swimming in "shools,"
you'd be smarter.


40
00:03:07.014 --> 00:03:08.391
The Go Fish Gang:
Megamind?!


41
00:03:08.433 --> 00:03:10.518
I knew it was only
a matter of time


42
00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:12.395
before the Go Fish Gang
tried to steal


43
00:03:12.437 --> 00:03:13.646
the diamond-encrusted koi

44
00:03:13.688 --> 00:03:16.232
on loan from
the Beijing Water Palace.


45
00:03:16.274 --> 00:03:17.817
It's something the old evil me

46
00:03:17.859 --> 00:03:19.777
would've done
way back in the day.


47
00:03:19.819 --> 00:03:23.239
Sir, "way back in the day"
was just two days ago.


48
00:03:23.281 --> 00:03:26.576
That's all? Time certainly drags
when you're a good guy.


49
00:03:26.617 --> 00:03:28.453
Minion,
how could you possibly serve


50
00:03:28.494 --> 00:03:30.371
a bad guy who's turned hero?

51
00:03:30.413 --> 00:03:31.956
Quick correction there.

52
00:03:31.998 --> 00:03:35.251
Due to a cease-and-desist order
from popular fast food chain


53
00:03:35.293 --> 00:03:36.753
Mr. Minion's Meat-sicles,

54
00:03:36.794 --> 00:03:38.880
I can no longer
call myself Minion.


55
00:03:38.921 --> 00:03:40.882
So, Megamind gave me
a new name.


56
00:03:40.923 --> 00:03:43.760
Ol' Chum.
It means, "old friend."


57
00:03:45.219 --> 00:03:47.764
Yeah, well, chum also
means something else.


58
00:03:47.805 --> 00:03:49.599
Shark bait!

59
00:03:51.059 --> 00:03:53.853
Wait, chum means "shark bait"?

60
00:03:53.895 --> 00:03:55.688
Why, yes! Sharks love bait!

61
00:03:55.730 --> 00:03:57.356
It's a term of endearment.

62
00:03:57.398 --> 00:03:58.399
Aw!

63
00:04:00.276 --> 00:04:03.279
It looks like we're both
about to be shark bait!


64
00:04:03.321 --> 00:04:04.781
Not for long.

65
00:04:09.660 --> 00:04:11.829
Apex predators are
a whole lot cuter


66
00:04:11.871 --> 00:04:13.331
when you can put
them in your pocket.


67
00:04:13.373 --> 00:04:15.291
They're getting away, sir!

68
00:04:15.333 --> 00:04:16.626
**

69
00:04:16.667 --> 00:04:19.379
Brainbot 227,
launch Porta-Prison!


70
00:04:22.173 --> 00:04:24.300
- Huh?
- Hey! What's going on here?


71
00:04:24.342 --> 00:04:26.552
That oughta hold you
until we can transfer you


72
00:04:26.594 --> 00:04:27.678
to your fishbowls.

73
00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.348
In jail... Huh?

74
00:04:32.016 --> 00:04:33.684
Whoopsie.

75
00:04:33.726 --> 00:04:36.312
Chum, this is
beyond embarrassing! -


76
00:04:36.354 --> 00:04:37.688
Sorry, sir.

77
00:04:37.730 --> 00:04:40.691
Hey, Megamind! Your gadgets
are like the Titanic,


78
00:04:40.733 --> 00:04:42.193
a total disaster!

79
00:04:42.235 --> 00:04:44.028
Megamind: How dare you!

80
00:04:44.070 --> 00:04:46.781
The Titanic was a delight
for most of the journey.


81
00:04:46.823 --> 00:04:48.491
After them!

82
00:04:55.748 --> 00:04:57.583
They're in a fish tank!

83
00:05:05.717 --> 00:05:08.594
You were great villains,

84
00:05:08.636 --> 00:05:11.556
but as heroes,
you guys are all wet!


85
00:05:11.597 --> 00:05:13.307
Let's finish them off!

86
00:05:16.602 --> 00:05:18.855
Chum, cube me.

87
00:05:24.235 --> 00:05:25.361
- Huh?
- What the?


88
00:05:25.403 --> 00:05:26.946
Bullseye!

89
00:05:26.988 --> 00:05:29.198
Ha!

90
00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:30.867
Alley-oop.

91
00:05:36.289 --> 00:05:37.749
Whoa!

92
00:05:37.790 --> 00:05:39.542
Water in the hole!

93
00:05:39.584 --> 00:05:40.752
Huh?

94
00:05:51.262 --> 00:05:53.431
Chum:
Sir, those bystanders are about to get squished!


95
00:05:53.473 --> 00:05:55.850
It does not look
good for them.


96
00:05:55.892 --> 00:05:57.560
Oh, right! I'm a hero now.

97
00:05:57.602 --> 00:06:00.271
May I suggest
the portal bazooka?


98
00:06:00.521 --> 00:06:03.024
You read my mind, Chum.

99
00:06:08.696 --> 00:06:09.906
Kids: Yay!

100
00:06:17.997 --> 00:06:21.250
Ah, shark!

101
00:06:22.335 --> 00:06:25.463
Crime.
It's a hard halibut to break.


102
00:06:26.881 --> 00:06:28.674
Chum, make a note.
No more puns.


103
00:06:28.716 --> 00:06:31.260
They're beneath us.

104
00:06:31.302 --> 00:06:33.554
Halibut! Like the fish!

105
00:06:33.596 --> 00:06:36.391
Brilliant, sir!
Just brilliant!


106
00:06:36.432 --> 00:06:38.434
**

107
00:06:38.476 --> 00:06:40.478
And tell all your evil friends

108
00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:42.271
Metrocity has a new defender,

109
00:06:42.313 --> 00:06:45.525
and his name is Megamind!

110
00:06:48.277 --> 00:06:52.281
Aren't you forgetting
another defender, sir?


111
00:06:52.323 --> 00:06:53.616
Don't think so.

112
00:06:53.658 --> 00:06:55.451
You didn't, by chance,
forget about someone who,


113
00:06:55.493 --> 00:06:58.538
I don't know, say,
gallantly fought by your side?


114
00:06:59.163 --> 00:07:02.500
Ah, of course! How could
I have possibly forgotten?


115
00:07:02.542 --> 00:07:05.461
- Chum, my friend?
- Yes, sir?


116
00:07:06.963 --> 00:07:09.340
Fix Brainbot 227.

117
00:07:09.382 --> 00:07:11.467
That short-out was
a little embarrassing.


118
00:07:11.509 --> 00:07:15.346
Remember, I have a super
heroic image to maintain.


119
00:07:19.600 --> 00:07:23.187
Crime continues to plunge
since Megamind saved Metro city


120
00:07:23.229 --> 00:07:25.648
from the clutches of evil.
But now, villains,


121
00:07:25.690 --> 00:07:27.984
many who flew below
Metro Man's radar,


122
00:07:28.025 --> 00:07:29.444
are coming out of the woodwork.

123
00:07:29.485 --> 00:07:33.239
So far, our new blue hero
seems up to the task.


124
00:07:33.281 --> 00:07:36.242
And while many changes
are afoot in Metro City,


125
00:07:36.284 --> 00:07:40.246
the one constant is me,
Roxanne Ritchi,


126
00:07:40.288 --> 00:07:43.541
reporting on
the accomplishments of others.


127
00:07:43.583 --> 00:07:45.918
Huh. Honestly,
how did that sound? -


128
00:07:45.960 --> 00:07:48.713
Child:
Like you just realized you've lost all interest in your job,


129
00:07:48.755 --> 00:07:50.465
and you're going through
the motions.


130
00:07:50.506 --> 00:07:52.216
Other than that, slam dunk!

131
00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:54.510
- And you are?
- Keiko Morita,


132
00:07:54.552 --> 00:07:56.846
president of Megamind's
number-one streaming online


133
00:07:56.888 --> 00:07:58.264
fan club MegaWatch,

134
00:07:58.306 --> 00:08:00.516
covering all things blue
and super-heroic in Metro City.


135
00:08:00.558 --> 00:08:04.520
- Um... okay.
- Have time for a few questions?


136
00:08:04.562 --> 00:08:06.355
What is happening right now?

137
00:08:06.397 --> 00:08:08.733
Roxanne Ritchi,
you just helped Megamind


138
00:08:08.775 --> 00:08:10.068
save the city from Titan.

139
00:08:10.109 --> 00:08:11.903
So what's your
awesome next step?


140
00:08:11.944 --> 00:08:14.906
Next step?
A-And are you recording this?


141
00:08:14.947 --> 00:08:17.075
Don't worry, it's great!

142
00:08:17.116 --> 00:08:19.535
Obviously, you're too cool
to be just on television.


143
00:08:19.577 --> 00:08:22.038
You're a shark.
You have to keep moving, girl!


144
00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:25.750
- You gotta have a side hustle!
- You're not wrong.


145
00:08:26.209 --> 00:08:28.544
I don't know.
Reporting is important,


146
00:08:28.586 --> 00:08:31.130
but Megamind has been
a hero for only a few days,


147
00:08:31.172 --> 00:08:33.925
and he's already making
a big difference in this city.


148
00:08:33.966 --> 00:08:35.843
Can't help thinking
maybe there's a way


149
00:08:35.885 --> 00:08:37.929
I can be doing more, too.

150
00:08:38.679 --> 00:08:41.724
Wait, why am I telling you
this? How old are you again?


151
00:08:41.766 --> 00:08:43.476
- You first.
- TouchÃ©.


152
00:08:43.518 --> 00:08:46.104
What you need to do is find
the thing you wanna do


153
00:08:46.145 --> 00:08:48.106
and go for it.
Look at me!


154
00:08:48.147 --> 00:08:49.732
A few weeks ago,
I was a middle schooler


155
00:08:49.774 --> 00:08:51.234
sitting in detention. Now,

156
00:08:51.275 --> 00:08:54.028
I'm streaming a show with
a half-million subscribers.


157
00:08:54.070 --> 00:08:56.364
Did you say half million?

158
00:08:56.406 --> 00:08:58.157
That's like

159
00:08:58.199 --> 00:08:59.826
- not counting family and pets.
- Keiko Morita: Gotta go.


160
00:08:59.867 --> 00:09:02.578
Wanna get a better shot of
the ceremony before it starts.


161
00:09:02.620 --> 00:09:05.957
- Good talk though.
- Yeah! Good talk.


162
00:09:05.998 --> 00:09:07.625
Half million...

163
00:09:08.543 --> 00:09:12.255
For his ongoing heroic actions
as Metro's defender,


164
00:09:12.296 --> 00:09:15.842
- I award Megamind
the key to our fair city. -


165
00:09:15.883 --> 00:09:19.220
I-I mean,
why not, right? -


166
00:09:19.262 --> 00:09:21.472
- Crowd: Megamind! Megamind!
- Thank you, thank you.


167
00:09:21.514 --> 00:09:23.349
You're very kind.

168
00:09:28.563 --> 00:09:32.024
Chum, be a good assistant
and deal with this for me.


169
00:09:32.066 --> 00:09:35.278
Whoa!

170
00:09:35.319 --> 00:09:38.239
Been getting some feedback

171
00:09:38.281 --> 00:09:41.993
that some of my speeches have
been running a little long,


172
00:09:42.034 --> 00:09:44.037
so I cut this one down...

173
00:09:44.078 --> 00:09:45.705
...to step length.

174
00:09:46.956 --> 00:09:49.125
Since the dawn of time,

175
00:09:49.167 --> 00:09:52.295
man has been dealing
with good versus evil.


176
00:09:52.670 --> 00:09:55.590
Hey, Chum.
How's the new hero gig going?


177
00:09:56.716 --> 00:09:58.468
Everything's changed for him.

178
00:09:58.509 --> 00:10:01.637
- Me, not so much.
- I know what you mean.


179
00:10:01.679 --> 00:10:03.181
I thought I was more to him.

180
00:10:03.222 --> 00:10:05.850
I thought I was
like his sidekick.


181
00:10:05.892 --> 00:10:07.977
But he still just
sees me as the minion


182
00:10:08.019 --> 00:10:11.397
who fixes his brainbots
and washes his socks.


183
00:10:11.439 --> 00:10:14.400
You know, someone
very recently told me,


184
00:10:14.442 --> 00:10:16.736
if you know what you want,
go for it.


185
00:10:16.778 --> 00:10:20.823
So, tell Megamind you want
a promotion to sidekick.


186
00:10:20.865 --> 00:10:22.533
Oh, it's not
a minion's place to--


187
00:10:22.575 --> 00:10:24.619
Roxanne Ritchi:
But you're not a minion.


188
00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:26.120
You're more than that.

189
00:10:26.162 --> 00:10:27.789
Maybe you just need
to remind him


190
00:10:27.830 --> 00:10:29.832
how valuable you really are.

191
00:10:29.874 --> 00:10:31.501
Speak from the heart.

192
00:10:31.542 --> 00:10:33.711
You're right.

193
00:10:33.753 --> 00:10:36.005
I need to speak from the heart.

194
00:10:36.047 --> 00:10:38.800
And that's why
you're all so lucky


195
00:10:38.841 --> 00:10:42.428
to have me as your hero.

196
00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:44.097
Megamind out!

197
00:10:45.139 --> 00:10:47.725
Uh! Excuse me!
Megamind?


198
00:10:47.767 --> 00:10:50.436
I'm Keiko Morita,
president of your fan club.


199
00:10:50.478 --> 00:10:53.481
President?
Oh, I have nothing but respect


200
00:10:53.523 --> 00:10:56.025
- for those who assume power.
- Then you'll love this.


201
00:10:56.067 --> 00:10:57.693
I'm also your new
social media manager,


202
00:10:57.735 --> 00:10:59.987
streaming content creator,
and image consultant.


203
00:11:00.029 --> 00:11:02.365
Those are a lot of words
I don't understand.


204
00:11:02.407 --> 00:11:04.117
Whoa! Is that
the disguise generator?


205
00:11:04.158 --> 00:11:06.160
- Can I try it?
- Don't touch that!


206
00:11:06.202 --> 00:11:08.663
It's a highly sophisticated
electronic device.


207
00:11:08.705 --> 00:11:11.040
It's cool! My generation
was born tech-savvy.


208
00:11:11.082 --> 00:11:14.544
Really? Then I suppose this is
one of those smarty-pants phones


209
00:11:14.585 --> 00:11:16.379
with a calculator
built right in.


210
00:11:16.421 --> 00:11:19.048
Okay, wow. That proves
you really need my help.


211
00:11:19.090 --> 00:11:21.092
You were threatening
the city a few days ago.


212
00:11:21.134 --> 00:11:22.468
Now you're defending it!

213
00:11:22.510 --> 00:11:25.179
People wanna know who
the new heroic Megamind is!


214
00:11:25.221 --> 00:11:27.265
I'll help you show them.

215
00:11:27.306 --> 00:11:28.599
You have a lot of energy.

216
00:11:28.641 --> 00:11:30.727
Did you just consume
a pound of sugar?


217
00:11:30.768 --> 00:11:32.311
Nope!
I'm like this naturally!


218
00:11:32.353 --> 00:11:34.272
Must be exhausting.

219
00:11:34.313 --> 00:11:36.899
I wanna be a crime fighter
just like you.


220
00:11:36.941 --> 00:11:38.359
You know, part of the team.

221
00:11:38.860 --> 00:11:40.737
Here's the thing.

222
00:11:40.778 --> 00:11:42.321
I don't do teams.

223
00:11:42.363 --> 00:11:43.990
I'm more of a solo act,

224
00:11:44.031 --> 00:11:46.743
but you're adorable
in a pushy sort of way.


225
00:11:46.784 --> 00:11:48.536
So, here's a souvenir.

226
00:11:48.578 --> 00:11:51.414
It's either a paperweight
or a flash grenade.


227
00:11:51.456 --> 00:11:54.709
I can't remember which,
so careful with that.


228
00:11:55.043 --> 00:11:56.627
He'll come around.

229
00:11:57.170 --> 00:11:59.464
Here he comes. You ready?

230
00:11:59.505 --> 00:12:00.590
Oh, absolutely!

231
00:12:00.631 --> 00:12:02.884
Had the brainbots
program an algorithm


232
00:12:02.925 --> 00:12:05.595
for a surefire
negotiation speech.


233
00:12:05.636 --> 00:12:08.139
Not what I meant by
speaking from the heart.


234
00:12:08.848 --> 00:12:11.601
Ah, there you are, Chum.
Let's head back to the lair.


235
00:12:11.642 --> 00:12:13.603
Those socks aren't
gonna wash themselves.


236
00:12:17.982 --> 00:12:19.859
Good afternoon!

237
00:12:19.901 --> 00:12:21.903
Do you aspire for success?

238
00:12:21.944 --> 00:12:23.112
I bet you do.

239
00:12:23.488 --> 00:12:26.574
Well, insert boss' name here,
while I humbly appreciate


240
00:12:26.616 --> 00:12:28.701
the opportunities
you've given me,


241
00:12:28.743 --> 00:12:31.996
since we've altered the mission
statement of our organization,


242
00:12:32.038 --> 00:12:34.123
I'm confident
I could achieve more.


243
00:12:34.165 --> 00:12:36.209
I believe I have made

244
00:12:36.250 --> 00:12:38.961
significant contributions
to the new paradigm


245
00:12:39.003 --> 00:12:41.255
and wish for
positional advancement


246
00:12:41.297 --> 00:12:43.966
befitting my more than
