00:13:47.321 --> 00:13:50.700
No, Roxanne!
Who am I to clip Chum's wings?


268
00:13:50.742 --> 00:13:54.203
I say fly,
you magnificent dove.


269
00:13:54.245 --> 00:13:56.873
Yes. I will fly.

270
00:13:57.331 --> 00:14:00.752
I thank you for all
the good times we had.


271
00:14:01.919 --> 00:14:05.256
We part now on friendly terms.

272
00:14:13.389 --> 00:14:15.058
I'll be a monkey's uncle!

273
00:14:15.099 --> 00:14:16.934
He's really
walking away this time!


274
00:14:16.976 --> 00:14:20.188
- I don't believe you.
- It's just a figure of speech.


275
00:14:20.229 --> 00:14:21.856
I'm not really
a monkey's uncle.


276
00:14:21.898 --> 00:14:25.401
I mean, I can't believe
you just let him quit!


277
00:14:25.443 --> 00:14:28.696
Relax.
It's a negotiation tactic.


278
00:14:28.738 --> 00:14:30.406
Like the time he went
on a hunger strike


279
00:14:30.448 --> 00:14:32.283
because he wanted
a pet parakeet.


280
00:14:32.325 --> 00:14:33.493
What did you do then?

281
00:14:33.534 --> 00:14:35.953
I waited him out
until he finally gave in.


282
00:14:35.995 --> 00:14:38.247
Parakeets are poop machines.

283
00:14:38.289 --> 00:14:40.750
Everything is changing so fast.

284
00:14:40.792 --> 00:14:44.837
Sometimes, I miss the simplicity
of the bad old days.


