working on an evil project.


494
00:24:51.152 --> 00:24:54.030
And that I'd signal them
when I took over Metrocity,

495
00:24:54.072 --> 00:24:56.199
which they think I have.

496
00:24:56.240 --> 00:24:58.951
Until I can figure out
a way to stop them,


497
00:24:58.993 --> 00:25:01.704
we must keep up
evil appearances.


498
00:25:01.746 --> 00:25:04.207
No. No! No way!

499
00:25:04.248 --> 00:25:07.085
Come on, Roxanne. Please?

500
00:25:07.126 --> 00:25:08.211
No!

501
00:25:08.586 --> 00:25:10.421
Pleas--

502
00:25:10.463 --> 00:25:12.548
And we're back.

503
00:25:12.590 --> 00:25:15.426
So, you guys have any schemes?

504
00:25:15.468 --> 00:25:18.179
I mean,
plans while you're in town?


505
00:25:18.221 --> 00:25:19.972
Nighty
-Knight: No,

506
00:25:20.014 --> 00:25:22.767
but this guy does!

507
00:25:22.809 --> 00:25:24.977
I'm not following.

508
00:25:25.019 --> 00:25:27.355
Lady Doppler:
We're here for Phase Two, silly.


509
00:25:27.397 --> 00:25:29.690
Phase Two.

510
00:25:29.732 --> 00:25:31.067
What's a Phase Two?

511
00:25:31.109 --> 00:25:34.237
Guess your boyfriend
doesn't tell you everything.


512
00:25:34.278 --> 00:25:36.948
Megamind said when
he took over Metro City,


513
00:25:36.989 --> 00:25:38.908
we'd all have a place
in the next phase


514
00:25:38.950 --> 00:25:40.827
of his evil master plan.

515
00:25:40.868 --> 00:25:43.913
Phase Two is
such a genius plan.


516
00:25:43.955 --> 00:25:46.708
I cannot wait to get started!

517
00:25:47.166 --> 00:25:49.585
Yeah! That's actually
one of the reasons


518
00:25:49.627 --> 00:25:51.337
why I agreed to evil-marry him.

519
00:25:51.379 --> 00:25:53.423
I love a good Phase Two.

520
00:25:53.464 --> 00:25:55.967
But, remind me again
what this one is


521
00:25:56.008 --> 00:25:58.094
and what havoc it might wreak?

522
00:25:58.136 --> 00:26:00.221
Would you give us a moment?

523
00:26:00.263 --> 00:26:03.057
Relax. I never even bothered
to finish Phase Two.


524
00:26:03.099 --> 00:26:05.184
Lady Doppler: Let's roll!

525
00:26:05.226 --> 00:26:07.437
What's the mad rush, guys?

526
00:26:07.478 --> 00:26:08.896
You just got here!

527
00:26:08.938 --> 00:26:11.816
Let's have some fun before
jumping into evil business.


528
00:26:11.858 --> 00:26:13.443
Charades, anyone?

529
00:26:13.818 --> 00:26:15.903
I say we break
in Megamind's city


530
00:26:15.945 --> 00:26:18.114
with a good old-fashioned
crime spree.


531
00:26:18.156 --> 00:26:19.157
Syndicate:
Yeah!


532
00:26:19.198 --> 00:26:21.242
I don't know, guys.

533
00:26:21.284 --> 00:26:23.995
Aren't we all a little above
crime spree-ing at this point?


534
00:26:24.037 --> 00:26:25.621
Syndicate:
No!


535
00:26:25.663 --> 00:26:28.207
Nighty-Knight:
Look out, Metro City, here comes the darkness.


536
00:26:28.249 --> 00:26:31.294
- Lady Doppler: Let's do this!
- Pierre: Away we go!


537
00:26:31.335 --> 00:26:34.630
What a fun and totally
preventable situation


538
00:26:34.672 --> 00:26:35.882
you've created.

539
00:26:35.923 --> 00:26:37.383
Please tell me you have a plan.

540
00:26:37.425 --> 00:26:39.135
Oh, you better warn the mayor.

541
00:26:39.177 --> 00:26:41.262
Meanwhile, I'll try to keep
The Doom Syndicate


542
00:26:41.304 --> 00:26:43.139
from destroying the entire city
while thinking of a plan


543
00:26:43.181 --> 00:26:44.640
to keep them from doing
my other plan.


544
00:26:44.682 --> 00:26:46.684
Make sense?

545
00:26:46.726 --> 00:26:48.227
Yes, but only in the

546
00:26:48.269 --> 00:26:50.146
you're-the-one-saying-it
sort of way.


547
00:26:51.272 --> 00:26:54.025
You should know
I'm a people non-person.


548
00:26:54.067 --> 00:26:55.234
I'm a self-starter,

549
00:26:55.276 --> 00:26:57.070
but also enjoy
the collaborative process.


550
00:26:57.111 --> 00:26:59.072
I'm proficient in
robotics, neuroscience,


551
00:26:59.113 --> 00:27:00.990
chemical engineering,
death-ray construction,


552
00:27:01.032 --> 00:27:03.034
bioengineering,
and event planning.


553
00:27:03.076 --> 00:27:05.078
So, anything in those areas.

554
00:27:07.246 --> 00:27:09.665
I'm lookin' for
a toilet scrubber.


555
00:27:09.707 --> 00:27:11.000
That's perfect!

556
00:27:11.042 --> 00:27:13.044
Another item
off my bucket list!


557
00:27:13.086 --> 00:27:15.922
I won't let you down, New Sir.

558
00:27:18.716 --> 00:27:21.386
Whoa! Ah!

559
00:27:36.317 --> 00:27:39.445
Today's forecast:
frigid cold flurries,


560
00:27:39.487 --> 00:27:42.365
and a hundred percent
chance of doom!


561
00:27:46.869 --> 00:27:49.747
Nighty-Knight:
That's a thunderstorm, not a snowstorm.


562
00:27:49.789 --> 00:27:52.500
Whatever, Mr. Nappy
-Nap.

563
00:27:52.542 --> 00:27:55.253
Behemoth: Behemoth hungry!

564
00:27:58.756 --> 00:28:01.926
It is just an advertisement,
you silly rock monster!


565
00:28:01.968 --> 00:28:03.469
**

566
00:28:03.511 --> 00:28:04.554
Huh?

567
00:28:04.929 --> 00:28:08.808
Flat man trick Behemoth!

568
00:28:15.273 --> 00:28:16.899
Officer:
Freeze! Police!


569
00:28:20.778 --> 00:28:22.363
You're all under arrest!

570
00:28:22.405 --> 00:28:23.573
**

571
00:28:23.614 --> 00:28:25.116
Now, officers,

572
00:28:25.158 --> 00:28:27.994
wouldn't you rather
just arrest yourselves? -


573
00:28:28.911 --> 00:28:32.123
Officers:
I have the right to remain silent.


574
00:28:32.165 --> 00:28:35.585
Anything I say can
and will be used against me


575
00:28:35.626 --> 00:28:37.587
in the court of law.

576
00:28:37.628 --> 00:28:39.630
- I have the right to a...
- Au revoir!


577
00:28:39.672 --> 00:28:42.258
Sorry about all this, officers.
We'll have a good chuckle


578
00:28:42.300 --> 00:28:44.719
when you snap out of it
in a few hours.


579
00:28:45.219 --> 00:28:46.804
Nighty-Knight:
The darkness!


580
00:28:48.473 --> 00:28:49.932
The bedlam!

581
00:28:51.059 --> 00:28:52.310
The chaos!

582
00:28:52.351 --> 00:28:55.146
I feed on it.

583
00:28:55.980 --> 00:28:58.149
Huh?

584
00:29:05.323 --> 00:29:09.035
I will call you
Mr. Cuddly Snuggles.


585
00:29:10.620 --> 00:29:13.247
No one must know
of our friendship.


586
00:29:14.123 --> 00:29:16.042
Darkness!

587
00:29:18.586 --> 00:29:19.670
Brainbots, code:

588
00:29:19.712 --> 00:29:20.963
"Fix all the things
the bad guys broke


589
00:29:21.005 --> 00:29:23.883
so I'm not legally
or financially responsible."


590
00:29:34.685 --> 00:29:35.520
That handles that!

591
00:29:36.479 --> 00:29:39.649
Mayor:
For his ongoing heroic actions as Metro's defender,


592
00:29:39.690 --> 00:29:43.319
I award Megamind
the key to our fair city.


593
00:29:45.279 --> 00:29:46.906
If only
your adoring public knew


594
00:29:46.948 --> 00:29:49.325
what we had
in store for everyone! -


595
00:29:51.953 --> 00:29:54.163
Yeah, poor them!

596
00:29:55.998 --> 00:29:58.668
Keiko: Whoa!

597
00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:01.796
Those guys are no joke!

598
00:30:09.387 --> 00:30:12.056
- Whoa! Close one!
- You again?


599
00:30:12.473 --> 00:30:14.100
Megamind just
saved yours truly


600
00:30:14.142 --> 00:30:16.227
from becoming
a human vegan pancake!


601
00:30:16.269 --> 00:30:18.604
For more awesome saves,
click like and subscribe!


602
00:30:19.814 --> 00:30:22.024
Oh-ho, my followers
are gonna love that!


603
00:30:22.066 --> 00:30:23.651
And you're much faster
than you look.


604
00:30:23.693 --> 00:30:26.320
Maybe it's the boots.

605
00:30:29.657 --> 00:30:31.576
You're gonna stop
those guys, right?


606
00:30:31.617 --> 00:30:34.037
Eventually, but right now,
I'm deep undercover.


607
00:30:34.078 --> 00:30:35.371
They still think I'm a villain.

608
00:30:35.413 --> 00:30:37.123
Cool! So, you need my help.

609
00:30:37.165 --> 00:30:38.624
I'll take the volcano guy!

610
00:30:38.666 --> 00:30:40.460
- No, here's what
you need to do. - Whoa!


611
00:30:40.501 --> 00:30:43.796
Use your super-tween speed to
run on home and watch cartoons.


612
00:30:43.838 --> 00:30:46.591
I'm more useful than
you think, you know!


613
00:30:46.632 --> 00:30:47.800
Ugh!

614
00:30:49.510 --> 00:30:51.387
Lady Doppler:
Look at that.


615
00:30:51.429 --> 00:30:53.890
A bank just waiting
to be robbed.


616
00:30:53.931 --> 00:30:56.350
Let's see some of that
old Megamind magic.


617
00:30:56.392 --> 00:30:58.561
Uh, no thanks. I'm good.

618
00:30:58.603 --> 00:31:00.063
Huh?

619
00:31:00.104 --> 00:31:01.731
I mean, I'm... not good.

620
00:31:01.773 --> 00:31:04.734
It's just important to
keep up good appearances.


621
00:31:04.776 --> 00:31:07.153
Remember, they still
think I'm a hero.


622
00:31:07.195 --> 00:31:09.072
What is ze point, eh?

623
00:31:09.113 --> 00:31:11.074
Phase Deux is just
around the corner.


624
00:31:11.115 --> 00:31:13.576
Nighty-Knight:
Robbing banks was like a ray of dark


625
00:31:13.618 --> 00:31:15.828
in your already
pitch-black soul.


626
00:31:15.870 --> 00:31:18.748
Aw, come on! Please?

627
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:20.917
Fine! I'll do it.

628
00:31:20.958 --> 00:31:23.795
Even though this sort of bad
is beneath me now.


629
00:31:30.760 --> 00:31:32.595
Bank Manager:
Look! It's Megamind! - Uh...


630
00:31:32.637 --> 00:31:35.306
The hero of Metro City!

631
00:31:35.348 --> 00:31:39.310
Oh no. Please! Your applause
really isn't necessary.


632
00:31:39.936 --> 00:31:43.064
Nighty-Knight:
I can't wait to see their faces when they realize


633
00:31:43.106 --> 00:31:45.316
evil Megamind is back.

634
00:31:45.358 --> 00:31:47.985
Their sorrow will be delicious.

635
00:31:48.027 --> 00:31:51.155
Their sorrow will be delicious.

636
00:31:51.197 --> 00:31:52.782
That's what you sound like.

637
00:31:53.366 --> 00:31:54.700
A few days ago,

638
00:31:54.742 --> 00:31:57.495
if you'd have come in,
I'd be hiding under my desk.


639
00:31:57.537 --> 00:32:01.124
Such a relief to know
you're on the good side now.


640
00:32:01.165 --> 00:32:03.251
**

641
00:32:03.292 --> 00:32:05.962
But no need to make a fuss.

642
00:32:06.003 --> 00:32:08.715
In fact, why don't you
all go back to treating me


643
00:32:08.756 --> 00:32:10.967
- like you did in
the bad old days. -


644
00:32:11.008 --> 00:32:13.469
But, that's when you were evil.

645
00:32:13.511 --> 00:32:15.179
You kept robbing us.

646
00:32:15.221 --> 00:32:17.640
That's not why
you're here, is it?


647
00:32:17.682 --> 00:32:20.101
I'm sorry.
I have to do this.


648
00:32:20.143 --> 00:32:21.602
B
-But why?

649
00:32:21.644 --> 00:32:25.189
Because it's, uh... it's, uh...

650
00:32:25.231 --> 00:32:27.316
- Keiko: It's a safety drill!
- Huh?


651
00:32:27.358 --> 00:32:29.777
For MegaWatch?
Half a million viewers?


652
00:32:29.819 --> 00:32:31.863
We're making this for the kids
at home so they know what to do


653
00:32:31.904 --> 00:32:34.949
in case a real villain
comes into the bank.


654
00:32:34.991 --> 00:32:36.701
Right, Megamind?

655
00:32:37.368 --> 00:32:38.911
Yes?

656
00:32:38.953 --> 00:32:40.163
I mean, yes!

657
00:32:40.204 --> 00:32:43.499
So, let's just pretend
it's like the old days.


658
00:32:43.541 --> 00:32:44.876
It'll be fun! Everyone,

659
00:32:44.917 --> 00:32:47.170
let's get those hands
in the air.


660
00:32:47.211 --> 00:32:48.838
Come on, get 'em up!

661
00:32:51.883 --> 00:32:53.176
Oh, I get it!

662
00:32:53.217 --> 00:32:54.594
Did I just save your butt?

663
00:32:54.635 --> 00:32:56.387
- Feels like I just
saved your butt. - Huh?


664
00:32:56.429 --> 00:32:58.347
Just need a quick pic
of the exact moment


665
00:32:58.389 --> 00:33:00.141
you realized you need me.

666
00:33:02.894 --> 00:33:05.188
I guess he is still
a master villain.


667
00:33:05.229 --> 00:33:07.482
Not only is
he robbing ze place,


668
00:33:07.523 --> 00:33:09.275
he's stopping for selfies!

669
00:33:09.317 --> 00:33:11.736
- Nighty-Knight: He hasn't lost
a dark and twisted step. -


670
00:33:11.778 --> 00:33:15.031
I still think
something's off about him.


671
00:33:15.073 --> 00:33:17.075
You are just jealous.

672
00:33:17.116 --> 00:33:18.701
Ze man is a genius!

673
00:33:18.743 --> 00:33:20.787
After all,
he left me in charge.


674
00:33:20.828 --> 00:33:23.915
Nighty-Knight:
What are you talking about? He put me in charge.


675
00:33:23.956 --> 00:33:28.711
He told Behemoth leader
should go by height and girth.


676
00:33:28.753 --> 00:33:31.214
Megamind:
Stay back!


677
00:33:31.255 --> 00:33:32.507
Stay back, I say!

678
00:33:32.548 --> 00:33:33.925
It certainly was good

679
00:33:33.966 --> 00:33:36.386
to work those old
bank-robbing muscles again.


680
00:33:36.427 --> 00:33:38.930
Okay, we need you
to settle something.


681
00:33:38.971 --> 00:33:41.432
Who did you leave in charge
of The Doom Syndicate?


682
00:33:41.474 --> 00:33:43.476
Uh, isn't it obvious?

683
00:33:43.518 --> 00:33:47.313
I chose the evilest
and most qualified candidate.


684
00:33:47.355 --> 00:33:48.940
All:
Thank you!


685
00:33:48.981 --> 00:33:51.025
- Wait?
- Huh?


686
00:33:51.484 --> 00:33:53.486
Mayor:
I'm getting calls from all over!


687
00:33:53.528 --> 00:33:55.405
People are saying
Megamind's running amok


688
00:33:55.446 --> 00:33:57.240
with a group of
villains out there!


689
00:33:57.281 --> 00:34:00.368
He's buying us time until he can
figure out a way to stop them.


690
00:34:00.410 --> 00:34:01.869
Mr. Mayor,
we have to trust him.


691
00:34:01.911 --> 00:34:04.414
We're still cleaning up
after the last time


692
00:34:04.455 --> 00:34:07.333
Megamind "saved" the city.

693
00:34:07.375 --> 00:34:09.293
I don't know what to do!

694
00:34:09.335 --> 00:34:12.588
Nobody told me mayor-ing
would be so hard!


695
00:34:12.630 --> 00:34:16.259
And I can't open
my tummy medicine!


696
00:34:17.802 --> 00:34:20.680
Thank you, Christina.

697
00:34:20.722 --> 00:34:24.142
Far be it from me to presume to
tell you what to do, Mr. Mayor.


698
00:34:24.183 --> 00:34:27.562
No, no, please! Presume away.
I-I got nothing!


699
00:34:27.603 --> 00:34:29.981
Well, first, you need
to notify law enforcement


700
00:34:30.022 --> 00:34:32.984
to pull back until Megamind
can figure out what to do.


701
00:34:33.025 --> 00:34:35.611
Then, get ahold of emergency
services and have them stand by


702
00:34:35.653 --> 00:34:39.073
- just in case things go wrong.
- Right. Got it.


703
00:34:40.658 --> 00:34:42.744
What did you say after, "first"?

704
00:34:42.785 --> 00:34:45.788
**

705
00:34:45.830 --> 00:34:49.000
Oh, you wouldn't
believe the day I had.


706
00:34:49.584 --> 00:34:52.754
They wouldn't
understand the new me.


707
00:34:52.795 --> 00:34:54.797
Not like you did, Chum.

708
00:34:55.882 --> 00:34:58.509
But I guess that's
all in the past.


709
00:34:58.551 --> 00:35:01.054
I'm defender of Metrocity now,

710
00:35:01.095 --> 00:35:05.308
and I need to learn to handle
these things on my own.


711
00:35:05.850 --> 00:35:09.437
But how do I take down
four villains at once?


712
00:35:09.479 --> 00:35:12.023
Maybe I just need
to sleep on this.


713
00:35:17.320 --> 00:35:18.905
Ah!

714
00:35:18.946 --> 00:35:21.407
What is that infernal racket?

715
00:35:28.956 --> 00:35:30.708
Woo!

716
00:35:36.506 --> 00:35:38.508
What in the name of
King Tut's cat collection


717
00:35:38.549 --> 00:35:39.801
is going on here?!

718
00:35:39.842 --> 00:35:42.095
Since we're launching
Phase Two tomorrow,


719
00:35:42.136 --> 00:35:46.015
we decided to throw
a Metro City's going-away party.


720
00:35:46.057 --> 00:35:48.434
I didn't agree
to that timeline.


721
00:35:48.476 --> 00:35:50.520
And where did all
these people come from?


722
00:35:50.561 --> 00:35:52.063
Knighty-Night:
Don't worry.


723
00:35:52.105 --> 00:35:54.023
They're all dark
and dangerous criminals.


724
00:35:56.484 --> 00:35:59.695
- Ollo?
- Roxanne : I bought some time with the mayor.


725
00:35:59.737 --> 00:36:01.030
What's all that ruckus?

726
00:36:01.072 --> 00:36:03.574
I'm the victim of
an impromptu rager.


727
00:36:04.659 --> 00:36:05.743
Just a second, Roxanne.

728
00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:08.996
Sir, I'll have you know
that is my special chair!


729
00:36:09.038 --> 00:36:12.375
Off now!
Why aren't you using a coaster?


730
00:36:12.417 --> 00:36:14.627
I want everybody out of here!

731
00:36:14.669 --> 00:36:16.879
Ah, don't be
ze pooper of parties.


732
00:36:16.921 --> 00:36:19.215
Besides, we texted
some old friends


733
00:36:19.257 --> 00:36:20.508
who just broke outta prison.

734
00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:22.301
They should be here any minute!

735
00:36:22.343 --> 00:36:24.178
Old friends?

736
00:36:25.388 --> 00:36:26.681
Oh no!

737
00:36:26.723 --> 00:36:28.850
The Go Fish Gang
just walked in.


738
00:36:28.891 --> 00:36:30.893
If they tell the Syndicate
I'm really a hero


739
00:36:30.935 --> 00:36:33.146
and not a villain
pretending to be a hero,


740
00:36:33.187 --> 00:36:35.356
this could get ugly quick.

741
00:36:35.398 --> 00:36:37.150
There he is!

742
00:36:37.191 --> 00:36:38.401
Gotta go!

743
00:36:38.443 --> 00:36:40.236
Attention, everyone!

744
00:36:40.278 --> 00:36:41.696
I said attention!

745
00:36:43.448 --> 00:36:46.868
There's something you all
should know about your host.


746
00:36:47.994 --> 00:36:49.871
Brainbot, lay down a sick beat.

747
00:36:49.912 --> 00:36:51.581
- Big King Fish:
The truth about Megamind-- - Huh?


748
00:36:51.622 --> 00:36:52.623
Hey!

749
00:36:52.665 --> 00:36:54.250
Hey! What the--

750
00:36:54.292 --> 00:36:56.586
- Wish I didn't have
to resort to this. -


751
00:36:56.627 --> 00:36:58.755
**

752
00:37:04.302 --> 00:37:07.722
Uh, hold on! Y-You all
should know Megamind--


753
00:37:07.764 --> 00:37:09.807
Has had no formal
dance training!


754
00:37:11.225 --> 00:37:14.687
DJ, put another stanky
groove in my pocket.


755
00:37:19.317 --> 00:37:20.818
I'll take Megamind.

756
00:37:20.860 --> 00:37:23.863
You two get to that
microphone and warn everybody.


757
00:37:23.905 --> 00:37:26.491
- Blue Mackerel: Hey, look out!
- Red Snapper: Outta my way!


758
00:37:26.532 --> 00:37:28.785
**

759
00:37:33.581 --> 00:37:34.665
Ah!

760
00:37:34.707 --> 00:37:36.709
Hey! We've got
a dance-off over here!


761
00:37:43.466 --> 00:37:45.426
Stand still!

762
00:38:00.400 --> 00:38:01.943
Ooh! Ooh!

763
00:38:03.361 --> 00:38:06.614
Ah! Just... Gimme... One...

764
00:38:08.533 --> 00:38:10.785
**

765
00:38:11.536 --> 00:38:14.330
Get back here!

766
00:38:14.372 --> 00:38:16.958
Where'd he go?

767
00:38:20.586 --> 00:38:22.213
What the...?

768
00:38:32.807 --> 00:38:35.727
How many capes
can one guy have?


769
00:38:35.768 --> 00:38:36.894
Aha!

770
00:38:39.063 --> 00:38:42.483
4,987, but who's counting?

771
00:38:44.277 --> 00:38:45.486
One down, two to go.

772
00:38:52.493 --> 00:38:53.536
Aha!

773
00:38:55.580 --> 00:38:56.664
Oh!

774
00:39:02.670 --> 00:39:04.881
Oh no!

775
00:39:06.966 --> 00:39:09.552
Uh, don't mind me!
Just dropped a little plutonium!


776
00:39:11.137 --> 00:39:13.264
Blast you,
Newton's Laws of Motion!


777
00:39:17.310 --> 00:39:18.311
Gimme!

778
00:39:18.352 --> 00:39:21.230
Hey!
You have dislodged my beverage!


779
00:39:21.272 --> 00:39:24.901
Oh, um, sorry, Pierre,
but that ice cube's gone bad.


780
00:39:26.194 --> 00:39:27.236
Whoa!

781
00:39:37.372 --> 00:39:39.540
Order up.

782
00:39:40.875 --> 00:39:43.252
Hoo! That was a battle!

783
00:39:43.294 --> 00:39:46.089
But I was once again
victorious, New Sir.


784
00:39:46.130 --> 00:39:48.549
By the way, do you have
a few seconds to discuss


785
00:39:48.591 --> 00:39:50.385
some life-altering changes?

786
00:39:52.053 --> 00:39:55.014
Okay, I'll take your
simmering silence as a yes.


787
00:39:55.056 --> 00:39:58.476
Firstly, my keen eye for detail
has noticed that we only get


788
00:39:58.518 --> 00:40:00.019
two customers every day,

789
00:40:00.061 --> 00:40:02.772
Eccentric Eddie and his
pet cockroach Thaddeus.


790
00:40:03.856 --> 00:40:06.275
But what if we had
more customers?


791
00:40:06.317 --> 00:40:07.944
Now, I know what
you're gonna say.


792
00:40:07.985 --> 00:40:10.822
"Chum, how can I increase my cash flow

793
00:40:10.863 --> 00:40:12.990
in this treacherous economy?"

794
00:40:13.032 --> 00:40:15.451
Well, while I was
in my office just now,

795
00:40:15.493 --> 00:40:17.078
I came up with a few ideas.

796
00:40:17.120 --> 00:40:20.623
First, I'd recommend giving
the place a good scrubbing.


797
00:40:20.665 --> 00:40:23.167
Latest market research shows
people generally don't like


798
00:40:23.209 --> 00:40:25.920
sticking to chairs.
Second, let's face it.


799
00:40:25.962 --> 00:40:29.215
The kitchen staff is
horrendous, New Sir.


800
00:40:29.632 --> 00:40:32.260
- I am the kitchen staff.
- Chum: Oh!


801
00:40:33.928 --> 00:40:35.763
Which is a complete
and utter waste.


802
00:40:35.805 --> 00:40:37.473
With your radiant personality,

803
00:40:37.515 --> 00:40:39.892
you should be out here,
with the customers!


804
00:40:39.934 --> 00:40:42.353
And the fully automated
cooking system I've designed


805
00:40:42.395 --> 00:40:45.690
will allow you to fill this
place with your unique brand


806
00:40:45.732 --> 00:40:48.443
of customer service sunshine.

807
00:40:48.484 --> 00:40:49.694
And finally,

808
00:40:49.736 --> 00:40:51.904
I propose a menu change.

809
00:40:51.946 --> 00:40:54.073
We need to specialize!

810
00:40:54.115 --> 00:40:57.243
And what's the one food
everybody loves?


811
00:40:57.285 --> 00:40:58.619
Donuts!

812
00:41:00.788 --> 00:41:02.665
Say the word,
and I'll get started.


813
00:41:02.707 --> 00:41:03.916
Mm!

814
00:41:03.958 --> 00:41:06.586
You won't regret this, New Sir.

815
00:41:13.926 --> 00:41:15.720
Megamind?

816
00:41:16.220 --> 00:41:18.931
Ah! What's going on?

817
00:41:18.973 --> 00:41:22.185
This place is a wreck.
Was there some kind of battle?


818
00:41:22.226 --> 00:41:24.187
Just a dance one!

819
00:41:24.228 --> 00:41:27.565
Can you turn off
the music, please?!


820
00:41:27.607 --> 00:41:28.941
What music?

821
00:41:28.983 --> 00:41:31.527
Oh, that can't be good.

822
00:41:31.569 --> 00:41:33.196
Did you make muffins?

823
00:41:33.237 --> 00:41:35.198
Yeah, I'm trying new things.

824
00:41:35.239 --> 00:41:36.699
**

825
00:41:38.409 --> 00:41:40.995
Why are you mad
at my taste buds?!


826
00:41:41.037 --> 00:41:43.331
I said I was
"trying" new things.


827
00:41:43.373 --> 00:41:46.209
Ugh, maybe I should use
these on The Doom Syndicate.


828
00:41:46.250 --> 00:41:48.044
Still don't have a plan, huh?

829
00:41:48.086 --> 00:41:50.213
Have you tried just
telling them to leave?


830
00:41:50.254 --> 00:41:52.340
If I tell them to leave,
they'll ask why.


831
00:41:52.382 --> 00:41:54.384
And if I tell them why,
they'll get mad.


832
00:41:54.425 --> 00:41:56.803
And when villains get mad,
they break things.


833
00:41:56.844 --> 00:41:58.554
And the first thing
they'll break is me.


834
00:41:58.596 --> 00:42:01.974
And me is one of my favorite
things in the whole wide world!


835
00:42:02.016 --> 00:42:03.393
Yeah, well, we have to
think of something


836
00:42:03.434 --> 00:42:06.145
before they do whatever
this Phase Two thing is.


837
00:42:06.187 --> 00:42:08.398
The problem is
they're always together.


838
00:42:08.439 --> 00:42:11.776
I have to find a way to
take them all out at once.


839
00:42:11.818 --> 00:42:14.404
Behemoth:
Last night rocked!


840
00:42:14.445 --> 00:42:16.948
Roxanne's back. Yippee.

841
00:42:16.989 --> 00:42:19.575
Nighty-Knight:
Alright. Muffins!


842
00:42:19.617 --> 00:42:21.702
Well, now that we've celebrated--

843
00:42:21.744 --> 00:42:24.580
Nighty
-Knight: Oh, that's nasty.

844
00:42:24.622 --> 00:42:27.041
Now that we've celebrated
Megamind's triumph,


845
00:42:27.083 --> 00:42:29.419
surely it's time for Phase Two.

846
00:42:29.460 --> 00:42:31.504
Again, my evil hubby

847
00:42:31.546 --> 00:42:34.966
has so many amazing phases,
I get confused.


848
00:42:35.299 --> 00:42:39.137
- What exactly is Phase Two?
- Okay.


849
00:42:39.178 --> 00:42:42.306
Phase Two is
an ingenious plan I had


850
00:42:42.348 --> 00:42:44.434
to launch Metrocity
to the moon.


851
00:42:44.475 --> 00:42:47.478
You're joking, right?
How would that even work?


852
00:42:47.520 --> 00:42:50.565
Simple evil genius physics,
really.


853
00:42:53.901 --> 00:42:55.987
An energy force field
would entrap air


854
00:42:56.028 --> 00:42:57.739
and protect the populace
from G forces


855
00:42:57.780 --> 00:43:01.451
as rockets built beneath
the city would carry it up to


856
00:43:01.492 --> 00:43:04.245
and safely land on the moon.

857
00:43:07.457 --> 00:43:09.876
Syndicate:
Phase Two! Phase Two!


858
00:43:09.917 --> 00:43:12.587
Phase Two! Phase Two!

859
00:43:14.881 --> 00:43:16.883
There, we would establish
an entire planet


860
00:43:16.924 --> 00:43:18.926
devoted to evil-kind.

861
00:43:18.968 --> 00:43:20.636
Nighty-Knight:
Yeah, imagine.


862
00:43:20.678 --> 00:43:23.139
All of us living together,

863
00:43:23.181 --> 00:43:26.184
always for eternity.
Forever.


864
00:43:26.225 --> 00:43:28.895
Until the last star
falls from the heavens


865
00:43:28.936 --> 00:43:31.314
and beyond that.
Together.


866
00:43:31.355 --> 00:43:32.857
All of us.

867
00:43:32.899 --> 00:43:35.234
Just me and my evil friends,

868
00:43:35.276 --> 00:43:37.987
living in infinite darkness.

869
00:43:39.197 --> 00:43:41.365
Why do you have a teddy bear?

870
00:43:41.407 --> 00:43:44.494
Nighty-Knight: Give me back
Mr. Cuddly Snuggles!


871
00:43:44.535 --> 00:43:45.995
There, there.

872
00:43:46.037 --> 00:43:47.580
It's gonna be okay.

873
00:43:47.622 --> 00:43:50.458
Zee? Zis is why no one
thinks you are scary.


874
00:43:50.500 --> 00:43:53.252
Nighty-Knight:
Teddy bears aren't scary? Yeah.


875
00:43:53.294 --> 00:43:55.880
They only eat hikers, idiot!

876
00:43:58.091 --> 00:43:59.967
Getting back to
this plan of yours,


877
00:44:00.009 --> 00:44:02.678
just curious because
I am super into it.


878
00:44:02.720 --> 00:44:04.055
How would that even work?

879
00:44:04.097 --> 00:44:06.849
Just building the giant
rockets under the city


880
00:44:06.891 --> 00:44:08.518
would take years.

881
00:44:11.062 --> 00:44:12.772
Megamind:
Actually, it took six months.


882
00:44:12.814 --> 00:44:14.190
Construction moves pretty fast

883
00:44:14.232 --> 00:44:16.234
when you don't have to worry
about silly permits


884
00:44:16.275 --> 00:44:17.485
and union lunch breaks.

885
00:44:17.527 --> 00:44:20.113
One of the advantages
of being evil, I guess.


886
00:44:20.154 --> 00:44:21.739
Excuse us, guys.

887
00:44:23.116 --> 00:44:25.243
I thought you said you
never finished Phase Two.


888
00:44:25.284 --> 00:44:27.537
Still needs a couple
of coats of paint.


889
00:44:27.578 --> 00:44:30.415
Also, never totally
satisfied with the decor.


890
00:44:30.456 --> 00:44:32.667
Let's get in there
and launch those suckers.


891
00:44:32.709 --> 00:44:35.545
Syndicate:
Yeah!


892
00:44:35.586 --> 00:44:38.715
Uh, yeah. That'd be
in the launch room.


893
00:44:39.924 --> 00:44:42.051
Computer:
Password error. Access denied.


894
00:44:42.093 --> 00:44:45.096
Oh no,
I've forgotten the password!


895
00:44:45.138 --> 00:44:48.141
- Okay, plan's foiled.
Time to go! - Hold it!


896
00:44:48.182 --> 00:44:50.143
You forgot the password?

897
00:44:50.184 --> 00:44:51.477
Thought it was my birthday.

898
00:44:51.519 --> 00:44:53.604
Guess not. That's so like me!

899
00:44:53.646 --> 00:44:54.939
Can we go now?

900
00:44:54.981 --> 00:44:57.275
Actually, it's not like you.

901
00:44:57.316 --> 00:44:59.235
See? This is what
I'm talking about.


902
00:44:59.277 --> 00:45:02.113
He's been acting out of
character since we got here.


903
00:45:06.117 --> 00:45:09.370
How dare you imply
I have character.


904
00:45:09.412 --> 00:45:11.622
And who said you could
use my favorite mug?


905
00:45:11.664 --> 00:45:13.166
**

906
00:45:13.207 --> 00:45:15.418
Don't forget,
we've been waiting a long time


907
00:45:15.460 --> 00:45:17.545
for your plan here
to come to fruition.


908
00:45:17.587 --> 00:45:20.131
I don't think you wanna
disappoint your old friends.


909
00:45:20.173 --> 00:45:22.925
Yes, ominous warning noted.

910
00:45:22.967 --> 00:45:24.594
How's this for ominous?

911
00:45:24.635 --> 00:45:27.180
Either we launch
by the end of the day,


912
00:45:27.221 --> 00:45:29.348
or we level the city.

913
00:45:29.390 --> 00:45:30.600
Got it?

914
00:45:31.976 --> 00:45:34.604
Did you really
forget the password?


915
00:45:34.645 --> 00:45:35.480
Of course not.

916
00:45:35.521 --> 00:45:38.274
The password is THX8675309.

917
00:45:38.316 --> 00:45:40.109
It'd take an idiot
to forget that.


918
00:45:40.151 --> 00:45:41.611
We can't let them
launch the city,


919
00:45:41.652 --> 00:45:43.362
and we can't let them
destroy it.


920
00:45:43.404 --> 00:45:45.031
You have to do something.

921
00:45:45.073 --> 00:45:46.991
Yes, I've been wracking
my brilliant mind


922
00:45:47.033 --> 00:45:48.409
to come up with a plan.

923
00:45:48.451 --> 00:45:50.119
Titan was just one villain.

924
00:45:50.161 --> 00:45:52.872
This is a whole
syndicate of them.


925
00:45:52.914 --> 00:45:54.290
I can't beat them alone,
Roxanne.


926
00:45:54.332 --> 00:45:57.377
You don't have to.
You have me, and you have Chum.


927
00:45:57.418 --> 00:46:00.630
You just need to be willing
to ask for his help.


928
00:46:00.671 --> 00:46:02.465
Oh, I should have
never let him go.


929
00:46:02.507 --> 00:46:04.926
He's been by my side
through bad and good,


930
00:46:04.967 --> 00:46:06.928
never once asking me
for anything.


931
00:46:06.969 --> 00:46:08.471
Except for the parakeet.

932
00:46:08.513 --> 00:46:11.140
But again, they're
poop machines, Roxanne.


933
00:46:11.182 --> 00:46:12.892
Stay on topic.

934
00:46:12.934 --> 00:46:14.477
You're right.

935
00:46:14.519 --> 00:46:17.313
I need to let Chum
know I appreciate him,


936
00:46:17.355 --> 00:46:20.316
not just as a colleague,
but as a friend.


937
00:46:25.196 --> 00:46:27.031
Roxanne:
Chum's working here now?


938
00:46:27.281 --> 00:46:29.826
They called me
for a reference.


939
00:46:29.867 --> 00:46:31.160
Used to be a diner,

940
00:46:31.202 --> 00:46:32.787
but I don't remember
it being so popular.


941
00:46:32.829 --> 00:46:35.456
Just with the health department.
And cockroaches.


942
00:46:35.498 --> 00:46:37.333
Vile creatures!

943
00:46:37.375 --> 00:46:39.877
I despise them more than
button-down collars.


944
00:46:39.919 --> 00:46:44.340
Okay... guess I know what not
to get you for your birthday.


945
00:46:45.717 --> 00:46:46.676
Uh, excuse us?

946
00:46:46.718 --> 00:46:49.512
I'll try my best.
Name, please?


947
00:46:49.554 --> 00:46:52.932
Uh, Megamind,
defender of Metrocity.


948
00:46:52.974 --> 00:46:54.392
I'm kind of a big deal.

949
00:46:54.434 --> 00:46:57.186
Oh, I'm sorry, Mr. Deal.

950
00:46:57.228 --> 00:46:59.188
Your name's not on
the reservation list.


951
00:46:59.230 --> 00:47:01.357
Reservations? For donuts?

952
00:47:01.399 --> 00:47:04.152
We're not here to eat.
There's an emergency.


953
00:47:04.193 --> 00:47:06.821
Let me guess.
A fashion one?


954
00:47:06.863 --> 00:47:08.156
Excuse me?

955
00:47:08.197 --> 00:47:09.615
Ma'am, you give me no choice

956
00:47:09.657 --> 00:47:12.034
but to assert my
dominance upon you.


957
00:47:17.081 --> 00:47:18.791
Roxanne, it's no use.

958
00:47:18.833 --> 00:47:21.461
Clearly, this hostess is
trained in Krav Magoo.


959
00:47:21.502 --> 00:47:23.212
You guys having
a little trouble?


960
00:47:23.254 --> 00:47:24.881
How are you always around?!

961
00:47:24.922 --> 00:47:27.800
Us girls gotta have our
secrets, am I right?


962
00:47:27.842 --> 00:47:30.970
Seriously, dunno how you guys
survived this long without me.


963
00:47:31.012 --> 00:47:32.680
Think you can do better?

964
00:47:33.931 --> 00:47:36.893
Keiko Morita, MegaWatch.
You could let my friend in


965
00:47:36.934 --> 00:47:39.562
or I could post a scathing
review to my many followers


966
00:47:39.604 --> 00:47:42.231
mentioning the restaurant's
cockroach infestation.


967
00:47:42.273 --> 00:47:46.319
- Nice try, but we don't have
a cockroach infestation. -


968
00:47:48.112 --> 00:47:49.614
Ew! She's touching it!

969
00:47:49.655 --> 00:47:52.658
Keiko's hand modeling career
is over before it even started!


970
00:47:52.700 --> 00:47:55.411
He's harmless.
Just needed the distraction.


971
00:47:55.453 --> 00:47:57.872
- Thanks, Eccentric Eddie.
- I owe you one. -


972
00:47:57.914 --> 00:47:59.665
Don't mention it, kid!

973
00:47:59.707 --> 00:48:02.752
I remember when this place
used to be cool.


974
00:48:02.794 --> 00:48:04.003
**

975
00:48:04.045 --> 00:48:05.630
I don't approve
of your methods,


976
00:48:05.671 --> 00:48:07.507
but you're starting
to grow on me.


977
00:48:07.548 --> 00:48:09.717
Like a pleasant fungus.

978
00:48:11.260 --> 00:48:12.762
Wow.

979
00:48:12.804 --> 00:48:15.598
They've really
cleaned this place up!


980
00:48:16.933 --> 00:48:18.309
Chum:
Then he said,


981
00:48:18.351 --> 00:48:21.270
"Crime, it's a hard
halibut to break!"


982
00:48:23.314 --> 00:48:24.816
Previous Sir?

983
00:48:29.320 --> 00:48:30.822
What are you doing here?

984
00:48:30.863 --> 00:48:33.491
Oh, Chum.
What are the odds?


985
00:48:33.533 --> 00:48:36.828
Us running into each other
at my favorite eatery...


986
00:48:36.869 --> 00:48:40.331
that I've just walked into
for the first time.


987
00:48:41.874 --> 00:48:44.877
But, I'm not really
here for donuts.


988
00:48:44.919 --> 00:48:46.546
Oh, but do try one, sir.

989
00:48:48.005 --> 00:48:49.674
Chum, I came here to--

990
00:48:49.716 --> 00:48:52.969
Oh, my stars! It's like
a jamboree in my mouth!


991
00:48:53.219 --> 00:48:54.303
Mm.

992
00:48:54.345 --> 00:48:56.597
But, I came here to
tell you something


993
00:48:56.639 --> 00:48:59.475
that's not easy for me to say.

994
00:48:59.517 --> 00:49:03.104
I want you to know
I've always really appreciated--


995
00:49:03.146 --> 00:49:04.814
New Sir:
Chum, good buddy!


996
00:49:04.856 --> 00:49:06.149
Oh, uh, New Sir,

997
00:49:06.190 --> 00:49:09.068
this is my old boss,
Previous Sir.


998
00:49:09.110 --> 00:49:10.820
Pleasure to meet you.

999
00:49:10.862 --> 00:49:12.655
I go by Mr. Donut now.

1000
00:49:12.697 --> 00:49:14.574
It was Chum's idea,
and he's told me


1001
00:49:14.615 --> 00:49:16.826
some pretty great things
about you!


1002
00:49:16.868 --> 00:49:18.786
Guilty as charged.

1003
00:49:18.828 --> 00:49:21.664
Though a few were
just indictments. Wow.


1004
00:49:21.706 --> 00:49:25.168
It looks like he's getting
along rather well without me.


1005
00:49:25.209 --> 00:49:28.129
Chum is a dream come true!

1006
00:49:28.171 --> 00:49:30.882
Business is booming!
Check this out!


1007
00:49:30.923 --> 00:49:32.133
**

1008
00:49:32.175 --> 00:49:35.011
Not only has he fully
automated the kitchen...


1009
00:49:37.263 --> 00:49:41.434
...but he also came up with
the recipe for my secret glaze.


1010
00:49:41.476 --> 00:49:42.894
Mm!

1011
00:49:44.103 --> 00:49:45.396
Listen to me, kid,

1012
00:49:45.438 --> 00:49:47.482
I know I was a bit of
a grouch when you started.


1013
00:49:47.523 --> 00:49:49.817
You? New Sir, no!

1014
00:49:49.859 --> 00:49:52.111
No, no, no, it's true.
But I want you to know,


1015
00:49:52.153 --> 00:49:55.865
I appreciate everything you've
done for me as a colleague.


1016
00:49:55.907 --> 00:49:58.743
But more importantly,
as a friend.


1017
00:50:01.204 --> 00:50:03.247
- Oh. Uh...
- Mr. Donut: So,


1018
00:50:03.289 --> 00:50:05.333
I got you somethin'.

1019
00:50:05.375 --> 00:50:07.543
Your filthy unwashed apron?

1020
00:50:07.585 --> 00:50:08.878
But you cherish this!

1021
00:50:08.920 --> 00:50:12.715
And now, it's your
filthy unwashed apron.


1022
00:50:13.257 --> 00:50:14.675
Wow!

1023
00:50:20.723 --> 00:50:23.184
You were about to tell me
something, Previous Sir?


1024
00:50:23.226 --> 00:50:26.479
Yes.
I wanted you to know...


1025
00:50:28.189 --> 00:50:29.941
that I'm too late.

1026
00:50:29.982 --> 00:50:32.819
It's clear this is
where you belong now.


1027
00:50:32.860 --> 00:50:36.072
Just know letting you go
is the biggest regret


1028
00:50:36.114 --> 00:50:38.533
of my soon-to-be short life.

1029
00:50:38.574 --> 00:50:40.827
Previous Sir, are you
in some kind of trouble?


1030
00:50:41.452 --> 00:50:43.788
It's not your concern anymore.

1031
00:50:43.830 --> 00:50:48.292
Besides, it's nothing
I can't not handle on my own.


1032
00:50:48.334 --> 00:50:50.586
Goodbye, old friend.

1033
00:50:52.213 --> 00:50:54.132
Just do me one favor.

1034
00:50:55.133 --> 00:50:57.385
Be happy.

1035
00:51:05.101 --> 00:51:06.519
Where's Chum?

1036
00:51:07.520 --> 00:51:09.939
He's where
he truly belongs now.


1037
00:51:11.899 --> 00:51:14.569
I can't put
this off any longer.


1038
00:51:14.610 --> 00:51:16.446
I have to stop
The Doom Syndicate myself.


1039
00:51:16.487 --> 00:51:20.241
Even if it most certainly
leads to my demise.


1040
00:51:20.283 --> 00:51:21.492
Car.

1041
00:51:21.826 --> 00:51:23.786
What are you gonna do?

1042
00:51:23.828 --> 00:51:26.914
Hopefully come up
with a really good idea.


1043
00:51:26.956 --> 00:51:30.752
- That's all I got.
- Listen, you don't have to do this alone.


1044
00:51:30.793 --> 00:51:33.796
I'm the defender of
Metrocity, Roxanne.


1045
00:51:33.838 --> 00:51:36.549
If I don't look out for
this place, who will?


1046
00:51:38.843 --> 00:51:41.304
But, who's gonna
look out for him?


1047
00:51:43.848 --> 00:51:45.933
Announcer:
Welcome to Season 27


1048
00:51:45.975 --> 00:51:50.813
of "Crab Cake Wars:
Crustacean Devastation." -


1049
00:51:51.856 --> 00:51:53.733
- Six culinary...
- Megamind: Ollo.


1050
00:51:53.775 --> 00:51:56.152
And where have you been?

1051
00:51:56.194 --> 00:51:58.905
Oh, just reminiscing
about days gone by.


1052
00:51:58.946 --> 00:52:02.492
Fragmented memories
of the way we were.


1053
00:52:02.825 --> 00:52:06.746
- What's he talking about?
- Behemoth get the picture.


1054
00:52:07.163 --> 00:52:10.333
Picture...
That's the really good idea


1055
00:52:10.375 --> 00:52:11.959
I was looking for, Behemoth!

1056
00:52:12.001 --> 00:52:14.420
Since this is our
last night on Earth,


1057
00:52:14.462 --> 00:52:16.422
we should really get
a picture of all of us.


1058
00:52:16.464 --> 00:52:18.883
Brainbot 227?

1059
00:52:18.925 --> 00:52:21.052
Everybody squeeze in tight.

1060
00:52:21.094 --> 00:52:22.845
Come on! Don't be shy!

1061
00:52:22.887 --> 00:52:25.598
I really wanna
capture this moment.


1062
00:52:25.640 --> 00:52:27.225
Don't you wanna be in it?

1063
00:52:27.266 --> 00:52:28.559
Maybe the next one.

1064
00:52:28.601 --> 00:52:32.271
Come on! Let's get some
grimaces on those faces.


1065
00:52:33.689 --> 00:52:36.859
On a count of three,
everyone say, "Porta-Prison"!


1066
00:52:36.901 --> 00:52:39.737
Syndicate:
Three, two, one... Porta-Prison?


1067
00:52:39.779 --> 00:52:41.864
Wait!

1068
00:52:41.906 --> 00:52:44.534
And boom goes your
days of freedom!


1069
00:52:44.575 --> 00:52:46.702
Oh yeah! Aha! Ooh!

1070
00:52:46.744 --> 00:52:49.038
Nighty
-Knight: What's going on?

1071
00:52:49.080 --> 00:52:52.291
I'll tell you what's
going on you guys.


1072
00:52:52.333 --> 00:52:54.711
Prison uniforms!

1073
00:52:54.752 --> 00:52:56.796
If this is a joke,
it's not funny.


1074
00:52:56.838 --> 00:52:58.798
Not for you,
but I'll be laughing


1075
00:52:58.840 --> 00:53:01.259
your whole way back to prison.

1076
00:53:01.300 --> 00:53:03.761
Our patience is wearing thin.

1077
00:53:03.803 --> 00:53:05.596
You know what's
gonna make you thin?


1078
00:53:05.638 --> 00:53:06.889
Prison food!

1079
00:53:06.931 --> 00:53:08.474
I could do these all day,

1080
00:53:08.516 --> 00:53:10.184
so let's just cut to the chase.

1081
00:53:10.226 --> 00:53:12.395
I'm really a good guy!

1082
00:53:12.437 --> 00:53:14.856
A champion of justice. A hero!

1083
00:53:14.897 --> 00:53:17.024
No!

1084
00:53:17.066 --> 00:53:18.860
You watch your language
in front of Behemoth!


1085
00:53:18.901 --> 00:53:20.653
Nighty-Knight:
I have been noticing


1086
00:53:20.695 --> 00:53:22.864
Megamind acting strange lately,

1087
00:53:22.905 --> 00:53:25.241
- and not in a good, dark way.
- Oui!


1088
00:53:25.283 --> 00:53:29.412
Idiots! I've been saying
that the entire time!


1089
00:53:29.454 --> 00:53:31.247
If Megamind really hero,

1090
00:53:31.289 --> 00:53:35.334
why he not be honest
and tell old evil friends?


1091
00:53:35.376 --> 00:53:37.920
Because you'd all destroy me!

1092
00:53:37.962 --> 00:53:40.131
That's why you're
locked safely in a...


1093
00:53:41.924 --> 00:53:43.926
...malfunctioning Porta
-Prison?

1094
00:53:47.638 --> 00:53:50.683
Man, I really got you guys!

1095
00:53:50.725 --> 00:53:54.228
It's a prank, bros!
Now, who's hungry?


1096
00:53:54.270 --> 00:53:56.689
Oh, if it was a prank,
then why are you sweating?


1097
00:53:56.731 --> 00:53:59.567
Sweating? Who's sweating?

1098
00:54:01.277 --> 00:54:03.780
Blast you, sweat bead.
Don't do this to me!


1099
00:54:03.821 --> 00:54:05.782
Go back from whence you came!

1100
00:54:09.410 --> 00:54:13.581
Attention, everyone!
Megamind really is a hero!


1101
00:54:13.623 --> 00:54:15.917
He's not pretending!

1102
00:54:15.958 --> 00:54:17.210
Wait, how did we get here?

1103
00:54:17.251 --> 00:54:19.462
Nice of you to pop in.
Megamind's ours,


1104
00:54:19.504 --> 00:54:21.881
but feel free to enjoy the show.
Get him!


1105
00:54:28.721 --> 00:54:31.015
Everything hurts...

1106
00:54:33.226 --> 00:54:36.646
Nighty-Knight: Time to say,
"Nighty, night!"


1107
00:54:36.687 --> 00:54:37.814
See, guys?
In the proper context,


1108
00:54:37.855 --> 00:54:39.982
that name is frightening.

1109
00:54:44.821 --> 00:54:47.490
And where do you
zink you're going?


1110
00:54:58.084 --> 00:54:59.001
**

1111
00:54:59.043 --> 00:55:01.879
Ah! Special chair, eject!

1112
00:55:07.593 --> 00:55:09.345
**

1113
00:55:11.848 --> 00:55:15.184
Think you can just
run away from your problems?


1114
00:55:18.938 --> 00:55:22.775
Ha! No more Megamind!

1115
00:55:25.945 --> 00:55:29.615
With its hero dead,
Metro City belongs to us now.


1116
00:55:30.199 --> 00:55:33.411
But maybe it's time we relocated
to a better neighborhood.


1117
00:55:34.620 --> 00:55:36.372
Mongolia?

1118
00:55:36.414 --> 00:55:37.540
The moon, Behemoth.

1119
00:55:37.582 --> 00:55:39.459
I'm talking about the moon.

1120
00:55:52.930 --> 00:55:54.724
Special chair!

1121
00:55:54.766 --> 00:55:56.976
I failed you.

1122
00:55:58.603 --> 00:56:00.605
I failed everyone.

1123
00:56:09.030 --> 00:56:11.699
Take a right here.
Megamind's close.


1124
00:56:11.741 --> 00:56:13.242
Roxanne:
How do you know that?


1125
00:56:13.284 --> 00:56:15.119
The fan club pin I gave him
has a tracker in it.


1126
00:56:15.161 --> 00:56:17.997
Roxanne: That's pretty devious.

1127
00:56:18.039 --> 00:56:20.500
You are his number-one fan.

1128
00:56:21.292 --> 00:56:24.045
This is kind of
a sketchy neighborhood.


1129
00:56:24.087 --> 00:56:26.631
Going where the danger is
is part of our job.


1130
00:56:26.672 --> 00:56:28.841
Besides,
we've always got diplomacy.


1131
00:56:28.883 --> 00:56:31.010
Oh. Did you learn
that in school?


1132
00:56:31.052 --> 00:56:33.471
No, Diplomacy is just
what I call my bat.


1133
00:56:33.513 --> 00:56:36.933
- Keiko, I think
you're gonna fit in just fine. -


1134
00:56:36.974 --> 00:56:39.685
Stop the van!

1135
00:56:52.657 --> 00:56:54.575
Megamind...

1136
00:56:55.118 --> 00:56:57.161
Megamind:
Never heard of him...


1137
00:57:04.001 --> 00:57:06.295
We've been looking for you
all over the city!


1138
00:57:06.337 --> 00:57:08.673
Wait, what's with
the fake beard?


1139
00:57:08.715 --> 00:57:11.175
You look like
a sad blue wizard.


1140
00:57:11.217 --> 00:57:14.095
Obviously, I'm hiding.

1141
00:57:14.137 --> 00:57:16.723
The city belongs to
The Doom Syndicate now.


1142
00:57:16.764 --> 00:57:19.350
Oh, here!
I have one for you, too.


1143
00:57:19.392 --> 00:57:20.351
We can be beard buddies.

1144
00:57:20.393 --> 00:57:21.978
I don't wanna
be beard buddies!


1145
00:57:22.019 --> 00:57:24.647
I want you to get off
your butt and save the city!


1146
00:57:24.689 --> 00:57:26.274
You're the only one who can.

1147
00:57:26.566 --> 00:57:28.192
Look, that's a nice sentiment,

1148
00:57:28.234 --> 00:57:30.236
but I've made a new life here.

1149
00:57:30.278 --> 00:57:33.614
Yeah. The piles of trash
really tie the alley together.


1150
00:57:33.656 --> 00:57:35.825
Thank you, Madam President.

1151
00:57:35.867 --> 00:57:37.869
Wait, how did you two
find me anyway?


1152
00:57:37.910 --> 00:57:40.413
Us girls gotta
have our secrets.


1153
00:57:40.455 --> 00:57:43.583
Well, that's adorable,
but there's no point.


1154
00:57:43.624 --> 00:57:45.585
I gave the hero thing a shot.

1155
00:57:46.044 --> 00:57:48.421
I can't protect this city.

1156
00:57:48.463 --> 00:57:49.881
I failed.

1157
00:57:49.922 --> 00:57:52.592
**

1158
00:57:52.633 --> 00:57:54.844
You didn't fail me.

1159
00:57:54.886 --> 00:57:55.970
What do you mean?

1160
00:57:56.304 --> 00:57:58.598
When I first moved to
Metro City with my mom,


1161
00:57:58.639 --> 00:58:00.475
I got teased a lot.

1162
00:58:00.516 --> 00:58:01.976
My name, the way I dressed,

1163
00:58:02.018 --> 00:58:04.187
the way I just say
whatever's on my mind.


1164
00:58:04.228 --> 00:58:05.772
I think being an outsider,

1165
00:58:05.813 --> 00:58:07.857
people just assumed
I was a bad kid.


1166
00:58:07.899 --> 00:58:10.359
I started being what
they expected of me,


1167
00:58:10.401 --> 00:58:12.528
getting into fights,
skipping class.


1168
00:58:12.570 --> 00:58:15.073
But then, you stopped Titan.

1169
00:58:15.782 --> 00:58:17.408
It showed me maybe
I don't have to live up


1170
00:58:17.450 --> 00:58:18.910
to others' expectations.

1171
00:58:18.951 --> 00:58:21.245
I just have to
live up to my own.


1172
00:58:21.287 --> 00:58:23.873
If a bad guy can become a hero,

1173
00:58:23.915 --> 00:58:26.000
maybe so can a bad kid.

1174
00:58:26.042 --> 00:58:27.627
Must be disappointing to see

1175
00:58:27.668 --> 00:58:30.421
your hero's such a fraidy-cat.

1176
00:58:30.463 --> 00:58:32.465
No! Shows you're smart!

1177
00:58:32.507 --> 00:58:34.258
Because you have zero
chance of defeating


1178
00:58:34.300 --> 00:58:35.927
The Doom Syndicate on your own.

1179
00:58:35.968 --> 00:58:37.637
I thought you
were my biggest fan.


1180
00:58:37.678 --> 00:58:40.014
I am, but I'm also a realist.

1181
00:58:40.056 --> 00:58:44.018
I'm both comforted
and confused by this pep talk.


1182
00:58:44.060 --> 00:58:46.354
Look, putting aside
your silly pride


1183
00:58:46.396 --> 00:58:49.023
and admitting you
need help is not weak.


1184
00:58:49.357 --> 00:58:51.734
I think you'll find
a true friend is with you,


1185
00:58:51.776 --> 00:58:52.985
no matter what.

1186
00:58:53.027 --> 00:58:54.737
You guys continue
your gooey moment.


1187
00:58:54.779 --> 00:58:56.656
I'm gonna go watch our six.

1188
00:59:00.326 --> 00:59:02.995
This is a big no-matter-what.

1189
00:59:03.287 --> 00:59:05.707
You get our backs,
we'll get yours.


1190
00:59:08.167 --> 00:59:11.087
Okay, but I've got
to find Chum.


1191
00:59:11.129 --> 00:59:13.172
I'm gonna tell him
I took him for granted.


1192
00:59:13.214 --> 00:59:15.091
He's more than a lackey to me.

1193
00:59:15.133 --> 00:59:17.093
He's a partner, a friend,

1194
00:59:17.135 --> 00:59:20.138
and I'm gonna ask for his help.

1195
00:59:20.179 --> 00:59:22.849
Chum:
You don't need to ask.


1196
00:59:22.890 --> 00:59:26.310
Chum?
What are you doing here?


1197
00:59:26.769 --> 00:59:28.438
My work is done with Mr. Donut.

1198
00:59:28.479 --> 00:59:31.315
But, Sir, my work is
never done with you.


1199
00:59:31.357 --> 00:59:33.735
Your constant state of chaos
makes me feel


1200
00:59:33.776 --> 00:59:35.611
as though I'm always needed.

1201
00:59:35.653 --> 00:59:39.031
You are, Ol' Chum. You are.

1202
00:59:39.073 --> 00:59:42.827
After all, what's a hero
without his sidekick?


1203
00:59:42.869 --> 00:59:45.204
Sidekick? Really, sir?

1204
00:59:45.246 --> 00:59:47.915
I can't tell you how long
I've waited for this!


1205
00:59:47.957 --> 00:59:49.000
Keiko:
Diplomacy!


1206
00:59:51.085 --> 00:59:52.879
Ah! I'm so sorry, Chum!

1207
00:59:52.920 --> 00:59:54.630
I didn't know it was you.

1208
00:59:54.672 --> 00:59:55.965
Big fan, by the way.

1209
00:59:56.007 --> 00:59:57.759
Chum:
Wonderful to meet you.


1210
00:59:59.469 --> 01:00:02.638
Nighty-Knight:
The darkness compels you to hit it harder.


1211
01:00:02.680 --> 01:00:04.766
Behemoth is hitting it harder!

1212
01:00:04.807 --> 01:00:06.726
Oh, how long is
this gonna take?


1213
01:00:06.768 --> 01:00:10.480
This titanium plating is
a formidable foe to our powers,


1214
01:00:10.521 --> 01:00:12.732
but, eventually, it will
yield to the darkness,


1215
01:00:12.774 --> 01:00:14.692
as all things do.

1216
01:00:14.901 --> 01:00:16.652
In non-goth speak, please?

1217
01:00:16.694 --> 01:00:19.405
Nighty-Knight:
About an hour if we don't break for snacks.


1218
01:00:20.740 --> 01:00:22.158
Chum:
By my calculations,


1219
01:00:22.200 --> 01:00:23.993
they should be able to break
through the security door


1220
01:00:24.035 --> 01:00:25.328
within the hour,

1221
01:00:25.370 --> 01:00:26.788
if they don't break for snacks.

1222
01:00:26.829 --> 01:00:28.331
We need to draw
The Doom Syndicate


1223
01:00:28.373 --> 01:00:30.375
away from those
launch controls.


1224
01:00:30.416 --> 01:00:31.584
A distraction.

1225
01:00:31.626 --> 01:00:33.795
Something they hate
with so much passion,


1226
01:00:33.836 --> 01:00:36.339
it overrides
their evil mission.


1227
01:00:36.381 --> 01:00:38.216
But what?

1228
01:00:41.010 --> 01:00:43.012
Right!
With all the excitement,


1229
01:00:43.054 --> 01:00:45.890
I forgot they want me dead!
What luck.


1230
01:00:46.182 --> 01:00:48.476
There is a second entrance
to the control room,


1231
01:00:48.518 --> 01:00:49.477
the air vent.

1232
01:00:49.519 --> 01:00:51.020
Can someone get in
through there?


1233
